I kinda drifted from my faith from junior high through high school. Not that I totally abandoned it, but comming right out of a Lutheran elementary school, I was surprised to see how &quot;free&quot; the other kids seemed to behave and it was attractive to me. Needless to say, I did some very unChristian-like things during that time.<br>
Thanks to places like Philisophia Christi, and the people there though, my faith has been rekindled from a candle to a bonfire, and I don't see myself ever leaving the LCMS.<br>
My girlfriend, on the other hand, is a Methodist, and it has been quite a struggle to correct her misunderstandings about the Lutheran church, e.g. she believes that Lutherans think they are the only ones going to heaven, etc...<br>
